      "parameters": [
        {
          "name": "pointInCollectionView",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "A point in the collection view’s coordinate system. Use this point to determine whether the drop would occur on an item or between items. "
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "return_value",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Return Value",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "A layout attributes object that identifies the element in which the drop would occur.  "
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The default implementation of this method tests the specified point to see if it lands inside an item, supplementary view, or decoration view of the collection view. If it does, the method returns the layout attributes for that element.  "
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Layouts that support inter-item gaps as drop targets must override this method and use it to return the layout attributes that represent that gap. In your implementation, calculate the index path just after the gap and pass that value to the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nscollectionviewlayoutattributes/1534062-layoutattributesforinteritemgapb"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " class method of "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": false,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nscollectionviewlayoutattributes"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ". Set the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nscollectionviewlayoutattributes/1532636-frame"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property of the resulting attributes object to the rectangle that best represents the gap and also contains the specified point. When overriding this method, you can call "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "super"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " at any time to get the default behavior. "
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
